**[1846, 04-15] Ms.B.1.6.2.19**

Estlin to May Jr.; Bristol

Various subjects; asks for figures on escaping slaves. “All the
information you send me on political and other matters, is very
acceptable to me. I do not now refer to them in particular. I wish I had
asked you a few questions on which I want information. One was, what is
the supposed,--the guessed at number of slaves actually escaping yearly
to Canada & the U. States?”


